The Labour Court has interdicted a planned strike in the banking sector, it says the proposed action is unlawful. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - The Labour Court has interdicted a planned strike in the banking sector, it says the proposed action is unlawful. Cosatu and Sasbo haveÂ been prevented from going ahead with a planned strike. Business Unity South Africa (Busa) brought the interdict against the trade unions, saying they have not negotiated with the banks before embarking on the strike. Unions will be urgently appealing the judgment and simultaneously approaching Nedlac for negotiations. The unions have encouraged their member to go to work on Friday and prepare for mobilisation in October.